      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "I AM HELLBOUND (4) made it two in wins succession at this venue when he came from wider than this and got the cash by close to 3 metres last week. That took his strike rate at the Menangle mile to 50 per cent. Draws to enjoy the favours so can land the hat trick. LONDON TO A BRICK (8) resumes from a spell of three-and-a-half months after placing in both outings of last preparation. Does tend to improve into his campaigns but two trial wins suggest he is back in good order. CONSTANTINOPLE (9) raced parked and boxed on for fourth last start. He is suited back to the mile having come from similar draws to this to win his previous two attempts here. PARAMOUNT KIWI NZ (1) started a hot favourite in his first outing for Jason Grimson but broke and lost his chance. He'll need to get it right from the inside draw but must be kept very safe. WATTS UP PARTYTIME (7) is another that can be hit-and miss on the manners front but he is talented and has won a trial since last seen.",
